{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NWeW8R45nb4Fb9vjB3jZJX","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive report.\n\n## Codebase Structure Analysis for Funnels Page Feature\n\nI've explored the codebase thoroughly. Here's a complete report on the structure, patterns, and key files:\n\n### 1. Package.json Scripts & Configuration\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/package.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"predev\": \"tsx scripts/migrate.ts\",\n    \"dev\": \"concurrently -n CH,NEXT -c cyan,green \\\"./clickhouse server -- --path=.clickhouse\\\" \\\"next dev\\\"\",\n    \"build\": \"next build\",\n    \"start\": \"next start\",\n    \"migrate\": \"tsx scripts/migrate.ts\",\n    \"lint\": \"biome check\",\n    \"lint:fix\": \"biome check --fix\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\",\n    \"typecheck\": \"tsc --noEmit\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n- Uses **Vitest** for testing\n- Uses **Biome** for linting\n- Uses **ClickHouse** (local server for dev)\n- Key dependencies: Next.js 16.2.3, React 19.2.4, Recharts 3.8.1, MUI 9.0.0\n\n### 2. Vitest Configuration\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/vitest.config.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport { defaultExclude, defineConfig } from \"vitest/config\";\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  test: {\n    environment: \"node\",\n    exclude: [...defaultExclude, \"playwright_tests/**/*.spec.ts\"],\n  },\n  resolve: {\n    alias: { \"@\": path.resolve(__dirname, \"src\") },\n  },\n});\n```\n\n- Uses Node environment by default (override with `// @vitest-environment jsdom` in component tests)\n- Import alias: `@` points to `src/`\n\n### 3. Existing Funnels Page\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/funnels/page.tsx`\n\nCurrently a stub:\n```typescript\nimport Typography from \"@mui/material/Typography\";\n\nexport default function FunnelsPage(): React.JSX.Element {\n  return (\n    <Typography variant=\"h4\" component=\"h1\">\n      Funnels\n    </Typography>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n### 4. Existing Funnels API Route\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/api/funnels/route.ts`\n\n- Implements POST `/api/funnels` endpoint\n- Validates request body: `{ steps: string[], start: string, end: string }`\n- Steps: 2-5 entries, non-empty strings\n- Dates: ISO format YYYY-MM-DD\n- Calls `queryFunnel()` from `@/lib/funnels`\n- Returns structured error responses (400/500)\n\n### 5. Funnels Library\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/lib/funnels.ts`\n\n**Key Types:**\n```typescript\nexport interface FunnelParams {\n  steps: string[];\n  start: string;\n  end: string;\n}\n\nexport interface FunnelStepResult {\n  name: string;\n  users: number;\n  conversion_from_prev: number | null;\n  conversion_overall: number;\n}\n\nexport interface FunnelResponse {\n  steps: FunnelStepResult[];\n}\n```\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `buildFunnelQuery(params)` - Constructs ClickHouse SQL with windowFunnel()\n- `queryFunnel(params, client?)` - Executes query, calculates conversions\n\n**Query Pattern:**\n- Uses `windowFunnel()` aggregate to track max level reached per user\n- Joins with identity_mappings for user_id resolution\n- Returns user counts with conversion_from_prev and conversion_overall\n\n### 6. Schema Cache Library\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/lib/schema-cache.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SchemaResponse {\n  event_names: string[];\n  properties: Record<string, Record<string, \"numeric\" | \"string\">>;\n}\n```\n\n- 60-second TTL cache\n- Functions: `getCachedSchema()`, `setCachedSchema()`, `invalidateSchemaCache()`\n- Used to prevent repeated /api/schema calls\n\n### 7. Trends Page (Reference Pattern)\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/trends/page.tsx`\n\n```typescript\n\"use client\";\n\nimport Box from \"@mui/material/Box\";\nimport Divider from \"@mui/material/Divider\";\nimport Typography from \"@mui/material/Typography\";\nimport { TrendChart } from \"@/components/TrendChart\";\nimport { TrendsControls } from \"@/components/trends/TrendsControls\";\nimport { useTrends } from \"@/components/trends/useTrends\";\n\nexport default function TrendsPage(): React.JSX.Element {\n  const { schema, controls, setters, series, numericProperties, loading } =\n    useTrends();\n\n  return (\n    <Box sx={{ p: 3, maxWidth: 1100 }}>\n      <Typography variant=\"h4\" component=\"h1\" gutterBottom>\n        Trends\n      </Typography>\n\n      <TrendsControls\n        schema={schema}\n        controls={controls}\n        setters={setters}\n        numericProperties={numericProperties}\n      />\n\n      <Divider sx={{ my: 3 }} />\n\n      <TrendChart series={series} loading={loading} />\n    </Box>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Patterns to replicate for Funnels:**\n- Use `\"use client\"` directive\n- Custom hook for state/logic (e.g., `useFunnels`)\n- Controls component separate from chart component\n- Box wrapper with `p: 3, maxWidth: 1100` styling\n- Loading state passed to chart\n\n### 8. Components Directory Structure\n\n```\nsrc/components/\n├── TrendChart.tsx                    (shared chart visualization)\n├── EventTable.tsx\n├── Sidebar.tsx\n├── ui/\n│   ├── JsonChip.tsx\n│   ├── IdentityChip.tsx\n│   └── __tests__/\n│       ├── IdentityChip.test.tsx\n│       └── JsonChip.test.tsx\n├── explore/\n│   ├── EventFilterBar.tsx\n│   ├── useEventExplorer.ts\n│   └── __tests__/\n│       ├── EventFilterBar.test.tsx\n│       └── useEventExplorer.test.ts\n├── trends/\n│   ├── TrendsControls.tsx            (controls UI component)\n│   ├── useTrends.ts                  (state management hook)\n│   └── __tests__/\n│       ├── TrendsControls.test.tsx\n│       └── useTrends.test.ts\n└── __tests__/\n    └── TrendChart.test.tsx\n```\n\n**Naming conventions:**\n- Component files: PascalCase.tsx\n- Hook files: camelCase.ts\n- Test files: same name + .test.tsx/.test.ts\n- Test directories: `__tests__/` at same level as source\n\n### 9. TrendChart Component Pattern\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/components/TrendChart.tsx`\n\n**Key Features:**\n- `\"use client\"` directive\n- Props: `{ series: Series[], loading: boolean }`\n- Chart type toggle: Line, Bar, Area, Table\n- Auto-switches to Bar when single data point\n- Renders Skeleton during loading\n- Empty state with \"No data\" message\n- Data transformation: `toRechartsData()` flattens series into date-keyed rows\n- Color palette: array of 8 distinct colors\n- ResponsiveContainer height: 300px\n\n**Test Patterns:**\n- Mocks recharts components (ResponsiveContainer, LineChart, etc.)\n- Uses `@vitest-environment jsdom`\n- Tests rendering, state changes, loading/empty states\n- Checks data-testid attributes\n\n### 10. TrendsControls Component\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/components/trends/TrendsControls.tsx`\n\n**Props:**\n```typescript\ninterface TrendsControlsProps {\n  schema: SchemaResponse | null;\n  controls: UseTrendsControls;\n  setters: UseTrendsSetters;\n  numericProperties: string[];\n}\n```\n\n**UI Elements:**\n- Event name Autocomplete (options from schema.event_names)\n- Measure Select dropdown: Count, Unique Users, Sum/Avg/Min/Max of property\n- Conditional Property Autocomplete (only for aggregations)\n- Granularity toggle buttons: Day, Week\n- Date range preset chips: 7d, 30d, 90d\n- Custom date pickers: Start/End\n- Breakdown Autocomplete (optional, filters by event properties)\n- Breakdown Limit numeric input\n\n**Layout:** Stack with spacing={2}, horizontal flex sections for related controls\n\n### 11. useTrends Hook\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/components/trends/useTrends.ts`\n\n**Return type:**\n```typescript\nexport interface UseTrendsResult {\n  schema: SchemaResponse | null;\n  controls: UseTrendsControls;\n  setters: UseTrendsSetters;\n  series: Series[];\n  numericProperties: string[];\n  loading: boolean;\n  error: string | null;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Behaviors:**\n- Fetches `/api/schema` once on mount\n- Derives numericProperties via useMemo (filtered from schema)\n- Fetches `/api/trends` whenever controls change (only if eventName set)\n- Builds URL with query params: event_name, measure, granularity, start, end, breakdown, breakdown_limit\n- Handles errors gracefully (schema stays null, series becomes empty)\n\n### 12. Test Files Overview\n\n**Test locations & patterns:**\n- Route tests: `src/app/api/{feature}/__tests__/route.test.ts`\n- Integration tests: `src/app/api/{feature}/__tests__/route.integration.test.ts`\n- Component tests: `src/components/{feature}/__tests__/*.test.tsx`\n- Hook tests: `src/components/{feature}/__tests__/*.test.ts`\n\n**Key testing patterns:**\n\n**Route tests (vitest, node environment):**\n- Mock dependencies with `vi.hoisted()` + `vi.mock()`\n- Create test Request objects with JSON body\n- Test validation errors (400), success (200), exceptions (500)\n- Verify mocked function was called with correct params\n\n**Component tests (jsdom environment):**\n- Mock external libraries (recharts)\n- Use `@testing-library/react` with `render`, `fireEvent`, `screen`\n- Test data-testid attributes\n- Test user interactions (clicks, inputs)\n- Use `cleanup()` in afterEach\n\n**Hook tests (jsdom environment):**\n- Use `renderHook()` from @testing-library/react\n- Stub global fetch with `vi.stubGlobal()`\n- Use `waitFor()` to wait for async state updates\n- Test initial state, data fetching, error handling\n\n### 13. Trends Library (for reference)\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/lib/trends.ts`\n\n**Key Types:**\n```typescript\nexport interface Series {\n  label: string;\n  data: SeriesPoint[];\n}\n\nexport interface SeriesPoint {\n  date: string;\n  value: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `buildTrendsQuery()` - constructs SQL with aggregation functions\n- `queryTrends()` - executes, transforms raw rows into series\n- Handles breakdown with top-N + \"Other\" merging\n\n---\n\n## Summary: Patterns for Funnels Implementation\n\n1. **Page component** (`src/app/funnels/page.tsx`):\n   - \"use client\" directive\n   - Use custom hook `useFunnels()` for state\n   - Render FunnelsControls + FunnelsChart\n\n2. **Controls component** (`src/components/funnels/FunnelsControls.tsx`):\n   - Props: schema, controls, setters\n   - UI: Autocomplete for event names, inputs for funnel steps, date range selector\n\n3. **Chart component** (`src/components/funnels/FunnelsChart.tsx`):\n   - Props: steps (step results), loading\n   - Render: Table/Visualization of conversion funnel\n\n4. **Hook** (`src/components/funnels/useFunnels.ts`):\n   - State: selected steps, date range\n   - Fetch /api/funnels on controls change\n   - Return: schema, controls, setters, steps, loading, error\n\n5. **Tests**:\n   - Route: validate inputs, test POST /api/funnels\n   - Hook: test state management, fetch logic\n   - Components: test rendering, user interactions\n\nAll files are located under the paths shown above."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0e7de277-607b-42d2-9d00-d4050492645c","uuid":"cbf57e78-37bf-4cce-bc22-b711922a69a0","timestamp":"2026-04-15T17:03:50.900Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the codebase structure for implementing a Funnels page feature. Please explore and report on:\n\n1. The content of `package.json` (test commands, lint commands, build commands)\n2. The vitest config file (vitest.config.* or similar)\n3. The existing `src/app/funnels/page.tsx` file\n4. The existing `src/app/api/funnels/route.ts` file\n5. The existing `src/lib/funnels.ts` file\n6. The existing `src/lib/schema-cache.ts` file\n7. The `src/app/trends/page.tsx` file (as a pattern reference for the new Funnels page)\n8. The `src/components/` directory structure\n9. Any existing test files (look in `src/components/**/__tests__/` and similar)\n10. The `src/components/TrendChart.tsx` file (for chart pattern reference)\n11. The `src/app/trends/` directory for any components like TrendsControls\n\nPlease provide full file contents for all files found. I need to understand naming conventions, import patterns, testing patterns, and component structure.","agentId":"aef905b252e8d9de7","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive report.\n\n## Codebase Structure Analysis for Funnels Page Feature\n\nI've explored the codebase thoroughly. Here's a complete report on the structure, patterns, and key files:\n\n### 1. Package.json Scripts & Configuration\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/package.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"predev\": \"tsx scripts/migrate.ts\",\n    \"dev\": \"concurrently -n CH,NEXT -c cyan,green \\\"./clickhouse server -- --path=.clickhouse\\\" \\\"next dev\\\"\",\n    \"build\": \"next build\",\n    \"start\": \"next start\",\n    \"migrate\": \"tsx scripts/migrate.ts\",\n    \"lint\": \"biome check\",\n    \"lint:fix\": \"biome check --fix\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\",\n    \"typecheck\": \"tsc --noEmit\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n- Uses **Vitest** for testing\n- Uses **Biome** for linting\n- Uses **ClickHouse** (local server for dev)\n- Key dependencies: Next.js 16.2.3, React 19.2.4, Recharts 3.8.1, MUI 9.0.0\n\n### 2. Vitest Configuration\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/vitest.config.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport { defaultExclude, defineConfig } from \"vitest/config\";\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  test: {\n    environment: \"node\",\n    exclude: [...defaultExclude, \"playwright_tests/**/*.spec.ts\"],\n  },\n  resolve: {\n    alias: { \"@\": path.resolve(__dirname, \"src\") },\n  },\n});\n```\n\n- Uses Node environment by default (override with `// @vitest-environment jsdom` in component tests)\n- Import alias: `@` points to `src/`\n\n### 3. Existing Funnels Page\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/funnels/page.tsx`\n\nCurrently a stub:\n```typescript\nimport Typography from \"@mui/material/Typography\";\n\nexport default function FunnelsPage(): React.JSX.Element {\n  return (\n    <Typography variant=\"h4\" component=\"h1\">\n      Funnels\n    </Typography>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n### 4. Existing Funnels API Route\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/api/funnels/route.ts`\n\n- Implements POST `/api/funnels` endpoint\n- Validates request body: `{ steps: string[], start: string, end: string }`\n- Steps: 2-5 entries, non-empty strings\n- Dates: ISO format YYYY-MM-DD\n- Calls `queryFunnel()` from `@/lib/funnels`\n- Returns structured error responses (400/500)\n\n### 5. Funnels Library\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/lib/funnels.ts`\n\n**Key Types:**\n```typescript\nexport interface FunnelParams {\n  steps: string[];\n  start: string;\n  end: string;\n}\n\nexport interface FunnelStepResult {\n  name: string;\n  users: number;\n  conversion_from_prev: number | null;\n  conversion_overall: number;\n}\n\nexport interface FunnelResponse {\n  steps: FunnelStepResult[];\n}\n```\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `buildFunnelQuery(params)` - Constructs ClickHouse SQL with windowFunnel()\n- `queryFunnel(params, client?)` - Executes query, calculates conversions\n\n**Query Pattern:**\n- Uses `windowFunnel()` aggregate to track max level reached per user\n- Joins with identity_mappings for user_id resolution\n- Returns user counts with conversion_from_prev and conversion_overall\n\n### 6. Schema Cache Library\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/lib/schema-cache.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SchemaResponse {\n  event_names: string[];\n  properties: Record<string, Record<string, \"numeric\" | \"string\">>;\n}\n```\n\n- 60-second TTL cache\n- Functions: `getCachedSchema()`, `setCachedSchema()`, `invalidateSchemaCache()`\n- Used to prevent repeated /api/schema calls\n\n### 7. Trends Page (Reference Pattern)\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/trends/page.tsx`\n\n```typescript\n\"use client\";\n\nimport Box from \"@mui/material/Box\";\nimport Divider from \"@mui/material/Divider\";\nimport Typography from \"@mui/material/Typography\";\nimport { TrendChart } from \"@/components/TrendChart\";\nimport { TrendsControls } from \"@/components/trends/TrendsControls\";\nimport { useTrends } from \"@/components/trends/useTrends\";\n\nexport default function TrendsPage(): React.JSX.Element {\n  const { schema, controls, setters, series, numericProperties, loading } =\n    useTrends();\n\n  return (\n    <Box sx={{ p: 3, maxWidth: 1100 }}>\n      <Typography variant=\"h4\" component=\"h1\" gutterBottom>\n        Trends\n      </Typography>\n\n      <TrendsControls\n        schema={schema}\n        controls={controls}\n        setters={setters}\n        numericProperties={numericProperties}\n      />\n\n      <Divider sx={{ my: 3 }} />\n\n      <TrendChart series={series} loading={loading} />\n    </Box>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Patterns to replicate for Funnels:**\n- Use `\"use client\"` directive\n- Custom hook for state/logic (e.g., `useFunnels`)\n- Controls component separate from chart component\n- Box wrapper with `p: 3, maxWidth: 1100` styling\n- Loading state passed to chart\n\n### 8. Components Directory Structure\n\n```\nsrc/components/\n├── TrendChart.tsx                    (shared chart visualization)\n├── EventTable.tsx\n├── Sidebar.tsx\n├── ui/\n│   ├── JsonChip.tsx\n│   ├── IdentityChip.tsx\n│   └── __tests__/\n│       ├── IdentityChip.test.tsx\n│       └── JsonChip.test.tsx\n├── explore/\n│   ├── EventFilterBar.tsx\n│   ├── useEventExplorer.ts\n│   └── __tests__/\n│       ├── EventFilterBar.test.tsx\n│       └── useEventExplorer.test.ts\n├── trends/\n│   ├── TrendsControls.tsx            (controls UI component)\n│   ├── useTrends.ts                  (state management hook)\n│   └── __tests__/\n│       ├── TrendsControls.test.tsx\n│       └── useTrends.test.ts\n└── __tests__/\n    └── TrendChart.test.tsx\n```\n\n**Naming conventions:**\n- Component files: PascalCase.tsx\n- Hook files: camelCase.ts\n- Test files: same name + .test.tsx/.test.ts\n- Test directories: `__tests__/` at same level as source\n\n### 9. TrendChart Component Pattern\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/components/TrendChart.tsx`\n\n**Key Features:**\n- `\"use client\"` directive\n- Props: `{ series: Series[], loading: boolean }`\n- Chart type toggle: Line, Bar, Area, Table\n- Auto-switches to Bar when single data point\n- Renders Skeleton during loading\n- Empty state with \"No data\" message\n- Data transformation: `toRechartsData()` flattens series into date-keyed rows\n- Color palette: array of 8 distinct colors\n- ResponsiveContainer height: 300px\n\n**Test Patterns:**\n- Mocks recharts components (ResponsiveContainer, LineChart, etc.)\n- Uses `@vitest-environment jsdom`\n- Tests rendering, state changes, loading/empty states\n- Checks data-testid attributes\n\n### 10. TrendsControls Component\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/components/trends/TrendsControls.tsx`\n\n**Props:**\n```typescript\ninterface TrendsControlsProps {\n  schema: SchemaResponse | null;\n  controls: UseTrendsControls;\n  setters: UseTrendsSetters;\n  numericProperties: string[];\n}\n```\n\n**UI Elements:**\n- Event name Autocomplete (options from schema.event_names)\n- Measure Select dropdown: Count, Unique Users, Sum/Avg/Min/Max of property\n- Conditional Property Autocomplete (only for aggregations)\n- Granularity toggle buttons: Day, Week\n- Date range preset chips: 7d, 30d, 90d\n- Custom date pickers: Start/End\n- Breakdown Autocomplete (optional, filters by event properties)\n- Breakdown Limit numeric input\n\n**Layout:** Stack with spacing={2}, horizontal flex sections for related controls\n\n### 11. useTrends Hook\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/components/trends/useTrends.ts`\n\n**Return type:**\n```typescript\nexport interface UseTrendsResult {\n  schema: SchemaResponse | null;\n  controls: UseTrendsControls;\n  setters: UseTrendsSetters;\n  series: Series[];\n  numericProperties: string[];\n  loading: boolean;\n  error: string | null;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Behaviors:**\n- Fetches `/api/schema` once on mount\n- Derives numericProperties via useMemo (filtered from schema)\n- Fetches `/api/trends` whenever controls change (only if eventName set)\n- Builds URL with query params: event_name, measure, granularity, start, end, breakdown, breakdown_limit\n- Handles errors gracefully (schema stays null, series becomes empty)\n\n### 12. Test Files Overview\n\n**Test locations & patterns:**\n- Route tests: `src/app/api/{feature}/__tests__/route.test.ts`\n- Integration tests: `src/app/api/{feature}/__tests__/route.integration.test.ts`\n- Component tests: `src/components/{feature}/__tests__/*.test.tsx`\n- Hook tests: `src/components/{feature}/__tests__/*.test.ts`\n\n**Key testing patterns:**\n\n**Route tests (vitest, node environment):**\n- Mock dependencies with `vi.hoisted()` + `vi.mock()`\n- Create test Request objects with JSON body\n- Test validation errors (400), success (200), exceptions (500)\n- Verify mocked function was called with correct params\n\n**Component tests (jsdom environment):**\n- Mock external libraries (recharts)\n- Use `@testing-library/react` with `render`, `fireEvent`, `screen`\n- Test data-testid attributes\n- Test user interactions (clicks, inputs)\n- Use `cleanup()` in afterEach\n\n**Hook tests (jsdom environment):**\n- Use `renderHook()` from @testing-library/react\n- Stub global fetch with `vi.stubGlobal()`\n- Use `waitFor()` to wait for async state updates\n- Test initial state, data fetching, error handling\n\n### 13. Trends Library (for reference)\n\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/lib/trends.ts`\n\n**Key Types:**\n```typescript\nexport interface Series {\n  label: string;\n  data: SeriesPoint[];\n}\n\nexport interface SeriesPoint {\n  date: string;\n  value: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `buildTrendsQuery()` - constructs SQL with aggregation functions\n- `queryTrends()` - executes, transforms raw rows into series\n- Handles breakdown with top-N + \"Other\" merging\n\n---\n\n## Summary: Patterns for Funnels Implementation\n\n1. **Page component** (`src/app/funnels/page.tsx`):\n   - \"use client\" directive\n   - Use custom hook `useFunnels()` for state\n   - Render FunnelsControls + FunnelsChart\n\n2. **Controls component** (`src/components/funnels/FunnelsControls.tsx`):\n   - Props: schema, controls, setters\n   - UI: Autocomplete for event names, inputs for funnel steps, date range selector\n\n3. **Chart component** (`src/components/funnels/FunnelsChart.tsx`):\n   - Props: steps (step results), loading\n   - Render: Table/Visualization of conversion funnel\n\n4. **Hook** (`src/components/funnels/useFunnels.ts`):\n   - State: selected steps, date range\n   - Fetch /api/funnels on controls change\n   - Return: schema, controls, setters, steps, loading, error\n\n5. **Tests**:\n   - Route: validate inputs, test POST /api/funnels\n   - Hook: test state management, fetch logic\n   - Components: test rendering, user interactions\n\nAll files are located under the paths shown above."}],"totalDurationMs":58221,"totalTokens":133038,"totalToolUseCount":24,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3093,"cac